molecules are formed by different chemical formation routes not directly\nlinked; although warm-up timescales effects and different formation and\ndestruction efficiencies in the gas phase cannot be ruled out. The most likely\nformation route of EG is by combination of two CH$_{2}$OH radicals on dust\ngrains. We also favor that GA is formed via the solid-phase dimerization of the\nformyl radical HCO, and a chemical link between MF and DME.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Aug 2016 15:14:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-01"}
